PSYCHOLOGY OF WORK 
	industrial or organisational psychology - business x psychology
		how to improve job satisfaction - to make them more productive and decrease turnover to save costs 
			training and coaching 
	why do people work
		extrinsic motives - money, social approval 
		intrinsic motives - internal goals 
			- work ethic - "u work cause u want to contribute to society and family - if u dont work then u r a NEET"
			- self identity - u identify with what you do - information about personality and social status, living standard, if u a dumbasss 
			- self fulfillment - 
			- self worth - receiving respect and recognition of contribution at work 
			- social values of work - work helps to extend social network - 
				after u graduate - major source of friends is workplace - o damn - this helps extend your social network 
			- social roles - career helps define roles in society - what is expected of you 
		what is more important? - in the short run, extrinsic motive might work - but over the long term, intrinsic motivation works - need to improve their self worth and help build a social network 
				also has something to do with ranking - if VP and high salary, pay hike may not be the most important factor, intrinsic factors matter
			also applies to studying - dont just focus on the grades
	stages of career development - refer to slides for revision 
		growth stage - 0-14
			fantasy stage - 
