	how to find the right job 
		Holland's person environment fit model
			your personal orientation
				needs 
				interests, values, personality 
			work environment	
				characteristics of work culture and environment 
					work a lot or good work-life balance 
			collection of these 2 aspects 
			you need to find a match  between the 2-  if you do then you are more satisfied, will have stable career 
			RIASEC - personal orientation 
				realistic - values concrete and physical tasks, lack social values, 
				investigative - problem solvers, systematic and curious and methodical, 
				artistic - want to express ideas freely 
				social - enjoy social involvement, exclusive with realistic people, i.e. guy cant be social and realistic 
				enterprising - influencers, leaders, decision makers - assholes irl - 
				conventional - orderly, systematic and concrete tasks, conformists - want fixed patterns in life - mutually exclusive with artistic people 
			first find personal orientation and find job that matches that 
			find jobs using psych test 
				vocational preference inventory - receive profile of 6 different orientations
				strong interest inventory - focus is on what people like - what they are interested in 
				MBTI - characterises people into 16 different types 
					measures ppl on 4 different dimensions 
					should we allow for continuity in types or discretize 
					MBTI - discretizes 
